LOL!

In addition to being quite funny, if you can imagine the Monty
Pythonesque scene as each and every one of the Buddhas highest ranking
monks bows out of the simple task of inquiring as to layman
boddhisatva's health because he has taken each and every one them up a
notch and out of their comfort zone at some point along the way, this
opening piece also lays the way for the Chinese sensibility of placing
lay person's practice on equal terms with monks. It also lays the
philosophical groundwork for the Mahayana ideal of the Buddha not
living in solitary retreat with other monks but returning to dwell
interact amongst the common people. Another sensibility probably
Chinese influenced and probably related with the closer attention to
lay practice.

I'm a sucker for a good laugh so this chapter has always been my
favorite.

